quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  100,10,"and the secrets of the hearts will be brought to light?"
  100,11,"Indeed, their Lord is All-Aware of them on that Day."
  101,1,"The Striking Calamity!"
  101,2,"What is the Striking Calamity?"
  101,3,"How do you know what the Striking Calamity is?"
  101,4,"On that Day people will be like scattered moths,"
  101,5,"and the mountains will be like carded wool."
  101,6,"Then the one whose scales of good deeds are heavy,"
  101,7,"will have a pleasant life."
  101,8,"But the one whose scales of good deeds are light,"
  101,9,"his abode will be the abyss."
  101,10,"And how do you know what it is?"
  101,11,"It is a Blazing Fire."
  102,1,"Competition for worldly gains distracts you [from Allah],"
  102,2,"until you come to your graves."
  102,3,"No indeed! You will come to know."
  102,4,"Again no! You will come to know."
  102,5,"No indeed! If only you knew for certain."
  102,6,"You will surely see the Blazing Fire,"
  102,7,"Again, you will see it with absolute certainty."
  102,8,"Then on that Day you will surely be asked about your worldly pleasures."